Example 3.9 from Generalized Linear Mixed Models: Modern Concepts, Methods and Applications by Walter W. Stroup(p-118)

Source: R/Exam3.9.R
Exam3.9.Rd

Exam3.9 used to differentiate conditional and marginal binomial models with and without interaction for S2 variable.

References

  1. Stroup, W. W. (2012). Generalized Linear Mixed Models: Modern Concepts, Methods and Applications. CRC Press.

See also

DataSet3.2

Author

  1. Muhammad Yaseen (myaseen208@gmail.com)

  2. Adeela Munawar (adeela.uaf@gmail.com)

Examples

#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
## Binomial conditional GLMM without interaction, logit link
#-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
library(MASS)
DataSet3.2$trt <- factor( x  =  DataSet3.2$trt )
DataSet3.2$loc <- factor( x  =  DataSet3.2$loc )

Exam3.9.fm1   <-
  glmmPQL(
      fixed    =  S2/Nbin~trt
    , random   = ~1|loc
    , family   =  quasibinomial(link = "logit")
    , data     =  DataSet3.2
    , niter    = 10
    , verbose  = TRUE
  )
#> iteration 1
#> iteration 2
#> iteration 3
#> iteration 4
summary(Exam3.9.fm1)

##--- Normal Approximation
library(nlme)
Exam3.9fm2 <-
  lme(
      fixed       = S2/Nbin~trt
    , data        = DataSet3.2
    , random      = ~1|loc
    , method      = c("REML", "ML")[1]
  )

##---Binomial GLMM with interaction
Exam3.9fm3   <-
  glmmPQL(
      fixed       =  S2/Nbin~trt
    , random      = ~1|trt/loc
    , family      =  quasibinomial(link = "logit")
    , data        =  DataSet3.2
    , niter = 10
    , verbose = TRUE
  )
#> iteration 1
#> iteration 2
#> iteration 3
#> iteration 4
#> iteration 5
#> iteration 6

#> iteration 8

#> iteration 10

##---Binomial Marginal GLMM(assuming compound symmetry)
Exam3.9fm4   <-
  glmmPQL(
      fixed       =  S2/Nbin~trt
    , random      = ~1|loc
    , family      =  quasibinomial(link = "logit")
    , data        =  DataSet3.2
    , correlation =  corCompSymm(form = ~1|loc)
    , niter       = 10
    , verbose     = TRUE
  )
#> iteration 1
